```julia
function clean_column(col::String)
    return String(lowercase(col)) |> strip |> replace(" " => "_", "-" => "_")
end
```

This function defines a pipeline of operations to be performed on the input string `col`. It first lowercases the string, then strips any leading or trailing whitespace characters, and finally replaces spaces and hyphens with underscores. The result is returned as a new string.
